5bs.title: Convex set
5bs.clickbait: A set that contains all line segments between points in the set
5bs.text:
A convex set is a [-3jz] of [3w0 vectors] that contains all line segments between vectors in the set.  Formally, a set $S$ is convex if

$$\forall x, y \in S, \theta \in [0, 1]: \theta x + (1 - \theta) y \in S$$
